00:23:19.160 --> 00:23:22.180
I joined a laboratory as an undergraduate,

00:23:22.180 --> 00:23:25.980
and the guy I worked for
loved to explore new compounds

00:23:25.980 --> 00:23:28.840
and how they impacted thermogenesis.

00:23:28.840 --> 00:23:32.723
And so we looked at how
things like MDMA/Ecstasy,

00:23:33.590 --> 00:23:37.180
how antipsychotics, antidepressants,

00:23:37.180 --> 00:23:39.730
various weight loss drugs
that were on the market.

00:23:39.730 --> 00:23:42.270
How those impacted body temperature

00:23:42.270 --> 00:23:43.970
and fat loss and metabolism?

00:23:43.970 --> 00:23:45.440
And we just had so much fun doing it.

00:23:45.440 --> 00:23:48.540
So if you detect a smile on my face,

00:23:48.540 --> 00:23:50.000
that's what that's about.

00:23:50.000 --> 00:23:51.170
And I also learned a lot,

00:23:51.170 --> 00:23:53.450
and I also came to really appreciate

00:23:53.450 --> 00:23:56.430
that this tissue of our bodies,

00:23:56.430 --> 00:23:57.840
adipose tissue and fat,

00:23:57.840 --> 00:24:00.270
we think of as just this unfortunate thing

00:24:00.270 --> 00:24:03.340
that's like we're told
it's a core energy source

00:24:03.340 --> 00:24:06.227
if we ever entered a famine
and that's all true, et cetera.

00:24:06.227 --> 00:24:08.880
You come to realize that
the cells in our body,

00:24:08.880 --> 00:24:13.880
they are there as fuel for
the furnace of our body,

00:24:14.020 --> 00:24:15.901
which is our metabolism.

00:24:15.901 --> 00:24:17.850
And there's a third player.

00:24:17.850 --> 00:24:19.240
And that's where it
really gets interesting.

00:24:19.240 --> 00:24:22.790
That the nervous system,
neurons has the opportunity

00:24:22.790 --> 00:24:25.800
to turn up the intensity of that furnace.

00:24:25.800 --> 00:24:29.062
It has the opportunity to
increase the amount of heat

00:24:29.062 --> 00:24:32.530
that we produce and therefore
the amount of energy

00:24:32.530 --> 00:24:33.550
that we burn.

00:24:33.550 --> 00:24:36.600
And I was also really intrigued
by something which is that,

00:24:36.600 --> 00:24:38.450
growing up, I think we all know people

00:24:38.450 --> 00:24:42.820
who can eat a tone and never
seem to gain any body fat.

00:24:42.820 --> 00:24:44.660
Or people who seem to eat very little

00:24:44.660 --> 00:24:46.380
and seem to gain body fat very easily.

00:24:46.380 --> 00:24:47.367
And I was always intrigued by that.

00:24:47.367 --> 00:24:50.150
And it turns out there are a
number of different factors

00:24:50.150 --> 00:24:51.520
that relate to that.

00:24:51.520 --> 00:24:53.460
But the nervous system is the one

00:24:53.460 --> 00:24:55.320
that we can really control.

00:24:55.320 --> 00:24:56.910
Both through behaviors and what we eat,

00:24:56.910 --> 00:25:00.290
but also in terms of this thing
that we call thermogenesis.

00:25:00.290 --> 00:25:02.420
There was one particular
story I want to relate to,

00:25:02.420 --> 00:25:04.840
that does not suggest any protocol.

00:25:04.840 --> 00:25:06.470
In fact, I'm going to discourage you

00:25:06.470 --> 00:25:08.143
from following this protocol.

00:25:09.060 --> 00:25:13.330
Please do not try the compound
that I'm about to describe.

00:25:13.330 --> 00:25:16.290
One of the favorite things
that we like to do in that lab

00:25:16.290 --> 00:25:20.250
was to find rare compounds and test them.

00:25:20.250 --> 00:25:23.910
And at the time I was
reading about thermogenesis

00:25:23.910 --> 00:25:25.320
and I learned about a compound

00:25:25.320 --> 00:25:28.200
that was actually discovered
in the armory factories

00:25:28.200 --> 00:25:29.910
of World War II.

00:25:29.910 --> 00:25:33.890
And it was discovered
because women in particular

00:25:33.890 --> 00:25:36.080
who were working in these factories

00:25:36.080 --> 00:25:39.940
would take a brush and
dip it in a compound

00:25:39.940 --> 00:25:41.090
or a paint rather,

00:25:41.090 --> 00:25:44.140
and they would then paint
the numbers with a stencil

00:25:44.140 --> 00:25:48.830
onto things like bombs and
ammunition of various kinds.

00:25:48.830 --> 00:25:52.550
And they were losing weight like crazy.

00:25:52.550 --> 00:25:54.460
It turns out that occasionally
they'd lick the brush,

00:25:54.460 --> 00:25:57.120
and then they would go back
just to get a sharper point

00:25:57.120 --> 00:25:57.953
on the brush,

00:25:57.953 --> 00:26:01.260
and then they would paint
onto these various bullets

00:26:02.366 --> 00:26:03.490
and missiles and so forth.

00:26:03.490 --> 00:26:05.040
Bombs and so forth.

00:26:05.040 --> 00:26:07.340
And they started shedding
all their body fat.

00:26:07.340 --> 00:26:10.910
And many of them losed, excuse
me, lost a lot of weight,

00:26:10.910 --> 00:26:12.570
a significant portion of their weight

00:26:12.570 --> 00:26:14.430
without changing anything
else that they were doing,

00:26:14.430 --> 00:26:15.780
what they were eating, et cetera.

00:26:15.780 --> 00:26:17.410
It turned out that that compound

00:26:17.410 --> 00:26:21.210
is something called Dinitrophenol, DNP.

00:26:21.210 --> 00:26:26.210
And over the years Dinatrophenol,
DNP has gained popularity

00:26:27.880 --> 00:26:29.070
in some niche cultures,

00:26:29.070 --> 00:26:33.190
mainly bodybuilders, athletes
even in the modeling industry.

00:26:33.190 --> 00:26:37.030
It is a absolutely terrible
compound for anyone to use,

00:26:37.030 --> 00:26:41.110
because it's highly fatal
if your body temperature

00:26:41.110 --> 00:26:42.140
goes too high.

00:26:42.140 --> 00:26:43.500
Hyperthermia will kill you.

00:26:43.500 --> 00:26:47.210
And indeed many people have
died using Dinatrophenol

00:26:47.210 --> 00:26:49.680
as a weight loss drug or attempting

00:26:49.680 --> 00:26:51.410
to use it as a weight loss drug.

00:26:51.410 --> 00:26:54.840
But Dinitophenol really
illustrates a principle

00:26:54.840 --> 00:26:58.540
which is that your
metabolism includes things

00:26:58.540 --> 00:27:01.240
like thyroid hormone and
growth hormone, et cetera.

00:27:01.240 --> 00:27:03.290
But your body temperature

00:27:03.290 --> 00:27:06.800
and the way you utilize energy

00:27:06.800 --> 00:27:09.850
is controlled by your nervous system.

00:27:09.850 --> 00:27:14.550
And the way Dinatrophenol works
is by changing the neurons

00:27:14.550 --> 00:27:17.420
and the way that the
neurons that connect to fat

00:27:18.490 --> 00:27:21.190
change the way fat burns up.

00:27:21.190 --> 00:27:23.410
So we are not going to suggest,

00:27:23.410 --> 00:27:26.940
I am not suggesting that
you use Dinatrophenol.

00:27:27.788 --> 00:27:29.580
However, there are other things

00:27:29.580 --> 00:27:32.810
that you can do that can
change the relationship

00:27:32.810 --> 00:27:36.080
between these neurons
and the fat of your body

00:27:36.080 --> 00:27:40.607
in ways that can powerfully
accelerate fat loss.

00:27:40.607 --> 00:27:42.900
And I don't know why we don't
hear about these things more,

00:27:42.900 --> 00:27:45.240
but probably because most of what you see

00:27:45.240 --> 00:27:46.750
out there on the internet focuses

00:27:46.750 --> 00:27:48.880
more on what you could eat and should eat

00:27:48.880 --> 00:27:50.080
or shouldn't eat.

00:27:50.080 --> 00:27:52.440
It concentrates on exercise regimens

00:27:52.440 --> 00:27:54.350
which we will also talk about.

00:27:54.350 --> 00:27:57.230
But the burn factor,

00:27:57.230 --> 00:28:01.530
your thermogenic
environment is one of the,

00:28:01.530 --> 00:28:03.890
if not the most important factors

00:28:03.890 --> 00:28:06.020
in this business of fat loss.

00:28:06.020 --> 00:28:07.450
And since I'm a neuroscientist

00:28:07.450 --> 00:28:09.150
that's what we're going to talk about.

00:28:09.150 --> 00:28:11.270
So let's talk about fat utilization.

00:28:11.270 --> 00:28:15.060
Let's talk about how fat
is converted into energy

00:28:15.060 --> 00:28:18.955
which is sometimes also
called fat burning.

00:28:18.955 --> 00:28:20.830
What I'd like you to know

00:28:20.830 --> 00:28:23.320
is that this is a two-part process.

00:28:23.320 --> 00:28:24.153
Okay?

00:28:24.153 --> 00:28:27.250
In reality, there are
many biochemical steps.

00:28:27.250 --> 00:28:29.770
And if you log onto the internet,

00:28:29.770 --> 00:28:32.710
or you open up a textbook
and you want to learn about

00:28:33.700 --> 00:28:34.840
fat utilization,

00:28:34.840 --> 00:28:37.370
you're going to see a lot of chemistry.

00:28:37.370 --> 00:28:40.010
And I'm happy to go deep into
that chemistry if you like.

00:28:40.010 --> 00:28:42.270
But I think most of you
are probably interested

00:28:42.270 --> 00:28:44.520
in what are the leverage points?

00:28:44.520 --> 00:28:47.540
Where can you exert control
over this process in ways

00:28:47.540 --> 00:28:48.380
that benefit you?

00:28:48.380 --> 00:28:50.580
So I'm going to focus mainly on those.

00:28:50.580 --> 00:28:51.413
Okay?

00:28:51.413 --> 00:28:54.350
This is not to upset the aficionados

00:28:54.350 --> 00:28:57.823
and I will put in some
nomenclature, but here we go.

00:28:58.780 --> 00:29:00.530
There's two parts to this process.

00:29:00.530 --> 00:29:03.680
One, is fat mobilization.

00:29:03.680 --> 00:29:08.420
And the second is fat
oxidation or utilization.

00:29:08.420 --> 00:29:09.253
Okay?

00:29:09.253 --> 00:29:12.640
So the first thing that
has to happen for body fat

00:29:12.640 --> 00:29:16.410
to get burned up or used and reduced

00:29:16.410 --> 00:29:19.000
is that it has to get mobilized.

00:29:19.000 --> 00:29:21.400
And that's a process called lipolysis,

00:29:21.400 --> 00:29:24.350
but I actually don't care if
you know the name lipolysis,

00:29:24.350 --> 00:29:29.350
you just have to move that
fat out of the position

00:29:29.530 --> 00:29:30.370
that it's in.

00:29:30.370 --> 00:29:32.390
You have to get it out of the fat cells.

00:29:32.390 --> 00:29:33.223
All right?

00:29:33.223 --> 00:29:36.160
Fat cells can be visceral
around our visceral organs

00:29:36.160 --> 00:29:37.930
or they can be subcutaneous
under our skin.

00:29:37.930 --> 00:29:41.180
Most people are thinking
about subcutaneous fat

00:29:41.180 --> 00:29:42.950
when they think about fat.

00:29:42.950 --> 00:29:45.350
So here's the deal.

00:29:45.350 --> 00:29:47.870
And if you want more detail,

00:29:47.870 --> 00:29:50.630
great, I'll touch on that in a bit.

00:29:50.630 --> 00:29:54.310
But basically stored fat has two parts

00:29:54.310 --> 00:29:55.650
that are relevant here.

00:29:55.650 --> 00:29:57.280
It's got the fatty acid part,

00:29:57.280 --> 00:29:59.540
and that's the part
that your body can use.

00:29:59.540 --> 00:30:01.700
And that's attached to
something called glycerol

00:30:01.700 --> 00:30:03.550
and they're linked by a backbone.

00:30:03.550 --> 00:30:05.490
So already, probably too much
chemistry for both of you.

00:30:05.490 --> 00:30:07.820
But what you want is you
want to break the backbone.

00:30:07.820 --> 00:30:09.727
So if you just can
remember to mobilize fat,

00:30:09.727 --> 00:30:11.230
you got to break the backbone

00:30:11.230 --> 00:30:13.270
between glycerol and these fatty acids.

00:30:13.270 --> 00:30:14.103
Okay?

00:30:14.103 --> 00:30:16.322
That's accomplished by
an enzyme called lipase,

00:30:16.322 --> 00:30:17.960
but you can forget all that if you want.

00:30:17.960 --> 00:30:20.230
Remember, we're just
trying to mobilize fat.

00:30:20.230 --> 00:30:23.210
So the first step is to
get those fatty acids

00:30:23.210 --> 00:30:25.210
moving around in the bloodstream

00:30:25.210 --> 00:30:27.640
to get them out of those fat cells.

00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:32.640
And then they can travel
and be used for energy.

00:30:32.680 --> 00:30:33.980
And that second part,

00:30:33.980 --> 00:30:35.740
remember first part is mobilization.

00:30:35.740 --> 00:30:37.770
The second part is oxidation.

00:30:37.770 --> 00:30:39.160
Is then those fatty acids,

00:30:39.160 --> 00:30:40.930
those are potential fuel.

00:30:40.930 --> 00:30:42.090
They're just potential fuel,

00:30:42.090 --> 00:30:43.590
but you haven't burned the fat yet,

00:30:43.590 --> 00:30:46.040
you've just moved it
out of your fat cells.

00:30:46.040 --> 00:30:50.820
They're going to go into cells
that can use them for energy.

00:30:50.820 --> 00:30:53.260
And once they are inside those cells,

00:30:53.260 --> 00:30:55.230
they're still not burned up.

00:30:55.230 --> 00:30:56.550
You need to oxidize them.

00:30:56.550 --> 00:30:59.820
Think oxidation is the burnup part.

00:30:59.820 --> 00:31:04.160
They need to be moved
into the mitochondria

00:31:04.160 --> 00:31:07.470
and then they can be converted
into ATP into energy.

00:31:07.470 --> 00:31:09.180
So just to really zoom
out again to make sure

00:31:09.180 --> 00:31:10.020
I don't lose anybody.

00:31:10.020 --> 00:31:11.280
You got to mobilize the fat,

00:31:11.280 --> 00:31:13.360
then you have to oxidize the fat.

00:31:13.360 --> 00:31:14.670
In other words, you have to mobilize it,

00:31:14.670 --> 00:31:17.150
then you actually have to
convert it into energy.

00:31:17.150 --> 00:31:19.650
If you just mobilize it,

00:31:19.650 --> 00:31:21.360
and you don't convert it into energy,

00:31:21.360 --> 00:31:22.590
you don't oxidize it,

00:31:22.590 --> 00:31:25.020
it can be returned to body fat.

00:31:25.020 --> 00:31:28.530
And many of the things that
the nervous system can do,

00:31:28.530 --> 00:31:32.400
is to increase the mobilization of fat,

00:31:32.400 --> 00:31:35.220
but also the oxidation of fat.

00:31:35.220 --> 00:31:36.053
Okay?

00:31:36.053 --> 00:31:39.070
So you have two opportunities
to burn more fat,

00:31:39.070 --> 00:31:41.520
and both of those
opportunities are governed

00:31:41.520 --> 00:31:43.000
by your nervous system.

00:31:43.000 --> 00:31:46.051
By neurons that literally
send little wires

00:31:46.051 --> 00:31:50.320
that we call axons into
fat and release chemicals

00:31:50.320 --> 00:31:54.140
that provide a stimulus
for more of that fat

00:31:54.140 --> 00:31:55.620
to be mobilized,

00:31:55.620 --> 00:31:59.300
and then later for more of
that fat to be burned up.

00:31:59.300 --> 00:32:00.133
Okay?

00:32:00.133 --> 00:32:02.420
So we could go really deep on this,

00:32:02.420 --> 00:32:04.170
but I'm not going to go
much deeper than that,

00:32:04.170 --> 00:32:06.400
because this isn't a biochemistry

00:32:06.400 --> 00:32:08.690
of fatty acid metabolism lecture.

00:32:08.690 --> 00:32:11.500
This is about how to burn fat
using your nervous system.

00:32:11.500 --> 00:32:13.740
But remember, there's a mobilization step,

00:32:13.740 --> 00:32:15.610
and then there's an oxidation step.

00:32:15.610 --> 00:32:17.410
I think anyone of you,

00:32:17.410 --> 00:32:19.230
all of you should be
able to internalize that.

00:32:19.230 --> 00:32:21.720
Mobilize then oxidize.

00:32:21.720 --> 00:32:22.553
Okay?

00:32:22.553 --> 00:32:24.250
Mobilize then oxidize.

00:32:24.250 --> 00:32:27.140
So what are these neurons
that connect a fat doing?

00:32:27.140 --> 00:32:29.080
What are they releasing exactly?

00:32:29.080 --> 00:32:31.450
How do they actually
increase fat mobilization?

00:32:31.450 --> 00:32:33.950
And how do they increase fat oxidation?

00:32:33.950 --> 00:32:35.920
Burning of fat.

00:32:35.920 --> 00:32:39.050
Well, there are a couple
of things that they release

00:32:39.050 --> 00:32:40.710
that encourage that process.

00:32:40.710 --> 00:32:44.480
And the main one that you need
to know about is epinephrine

00:32:44.480 --> 00:32:46.130
or adrenaline.

00:32:46.130 --> 00:32:49.470
The conversion of these
fatty acids into ATP

00:32:49.470 --> 00:32:53.820
in the mitochondria of cells
is favored by adrenaline.

00:32:53.820 --> 00:32:54.700
Okay?

00:32:54.700 --> 00:32:58.340
And adrenaline is
released from two sources.

00:32:58.340 --> 00:33:00.450
Adrenaline is released
from the adrenal glands,

00:33:00.450 --> 00:33:03.410
which set a top our
kidneys and our lower back.

00:33:03.410 --> 00:33:05.560
And it's also released

00:33:05.560 --> 00:33:07.620
from the so-called
sympathetic nervous system.

00:33:07.620 --> 00:33:09.820
Although that name is a bit of a misnomer,

00:33:09.820 --> 00:33:11.940
because it has nothing
to do with sympathy,

00:33:11.940 --> 00:33:14.360
has to do with stimulating alertness

00:33:14.360 --> 00:33:16.793
and promoting action of the body.

00:33:17.800 --> 00:33:22.330
There's a big mistake in the literature

00:33:22.330 --> 00:33:25.899
that is finally being
corrected among those who know.

00:33:25.899 --> 00:33:29.410
The mistake in the literature
is that the adrenal glands

00:33:29.410 --> 00:33:33.380
and the release of adrenaline
is what stimulates fat loss

00:33:33.380 --> 00:33:35.360
and fat oxidation.

00:33:35.360 --> 00:33:37.950
In fact, it was thought for a long time

00:33:37.950 --> 00:33:40.130
that adrenaline swimming
around in your body

00:33:40.130 --> 00:33:41.440
of when you're fasted,

00:33:41.440 --> 00:33:43.510
because fasting can increase adrenaline

00:33:43.510 --> 00:33:46.330
or when you're engaging
in intense exercise

00:33:46.330 --> 00:33:50.260
or when you're stressed is
going to promote fat oxidation.

00:33:50.260 --> 00:33:52.103
That's actually not the case.

00:33:53.090 --> 00:33:56.400
The adrenaline that
stimulates fat oxidation,

00:33:56.400 --> 00:33:59.540
the burning of fat is coming from neurons

00:33:59.540 --> 00:34:02.670
that actually connect to the fat,

00:34:02.670 --> 00:34:05.820
not hormones like adrenaline
that are swimming around

00:34:05.820 --> 00:34:06.653
in your system.

00:34:06.653 --> 00:34:08.430
It's a local process.

00:34:08.430 --> 00:34:12.420
And this is very important
because it means that,

00:34:12.420 --> 00:34:16.410
what you do, the specific
patterns of movements

00:34:16.410 --> 00:34:19.353
and the specific environment you create

00:34:19.353 --> 00:34:24.353
that can stimulate these
particular neurons to activate fat,

00:34:26.120 --> 00:34:28.560
meaning to release fat,

00:34:28.560 --> 00:34:30.360
to mobilize it and then to burn it,

00:34:30.360 --> 00:34:33.210
is going to be a powerful
lever that you can use

00:34:33.210 --> 00:34:35.190
in order to increase fat loss.

00:34:35.190 --> 00:34:36.330
So what have we said so far?

00:34:36.330 --> 00:34:38.560
We've said that you've got to
mobilize and you got to burn fat

00:34:38.560 --> 00:34:42.870
and that your nervous system
is in control of that process.

00:34:42.870 --> 00:34:45.773
It's not just about calorie deficit.

00:34:46.710 --> 00:34:49.050
Okay, so let's talk about how to activate

00:34:49.050 --> 00:34:51.090
the nervous system in
ways that it promotes

00:34:51.090 --> 00:34:54.160
more liberation, movement,
mobilization of fat

00:34:54.160 --> 00:34:56.660
and more oxidation of fat.

00:34:56.660 --> 00:35:00.070
So one of the most powerful
ways to stimulate epinephrin

00:35:00.070 --> 00:35:02.750
which is also called
adrenaline from these neurons

00:35:02.750 --> 00:35:06.240
that connect to fat and
to thereby stimulate

00:35:06.240 --> 00:35:10.980
more fat mobilization and
oxidation is through movement.

00:35:10.980 --> 00:35:13.650
But I'm not talking about exercise.

00:35:13.650 --> 00:35:15.500
The type of movement
that I'm referring to,

00:35:15.500 --> 00:35:17.840
is extremely subtle.

00:35:17.840 --> 00:35:21.850
And some of you may be familiar
with this type of movement,

00:35:21.850 --> 00:35:24.900
but I'm guessing you're
probably not familiar

00:35:24.900 --> 00:35:26.590
with what I'm about to tell you,

00:35:26.590 --> 00:35:31.590
which is that shiver or
shivering is a strong stimulus

00:35:32.860 --> 00:35:36.660
for the release of adrenaline
epinephrin into fat

00:35:36.660 --> 00:35:41.090
and the increase in fat
