of any positive effects of iricin

00:59:54.000 --> 00:59:57.900
or of any signs of irisin
that I'm overlooking here,

00:59:57.900 --> 00:59:59.890
or that I'm speaking about
incorrectly, please let me know.

00:59:59.890 --> 01:00:02.290
I'd be very curious to learn.

01:00:02.290 --> 01:00:06.870
Now, I want to just talk about
brown fat a little bit more,

01:00:06.870 --> 01:00:09.194
and talk about a period in your life

01:00:09.194 --> 01:00:12.320
in which you were rich with brown fat,

01:00:12.320 --> 01:00:13.910
you had a ton of brown fat,

01:00:13.910 --> 01:00:16.340
and that's when you were a baby.

01:00:16.340 --> 01:00:18.243
Babies can't shiver.

01:00:19.280 --> 01:00:23.930
These neurons that release
epinephrin into fat

01:00:23.930 --> 01:00:27.830
are not wired up and really aren't present

01:00:27.830 --> 01:00:30.810
at sufficient levels or
in sufficient numbers

01:00:30.810 --> 01:00:32.320
when you are a baby.

01:00:32.320 --> 01:00:35.140
And therefore you can't shiver as a baby,

01:00:35.140 --> 01:00:37.310
and you can't warm yourself
up in cold environments

01:00:37.310 --> 01:00:38.870
very well.

01:00:38.870 --> 01:00:40.313
To compensate for that,

01:00:41.440 --> 01:00:44.180
mother nature installed in all of us

01:00:44.180 --> 01:00:47.280
an excess of brown fat early in life

01:00:47.280 --> 01:00:49.337
that exists again in the upper back,

01:00:49.337 --> 01:00:51.937
and the middle of the back
and the back of the neck.

01:00:53.250 --> 01:00:57.250
Over time if we don't expose
ourselves to cold environments

01:00:57.250 --> 01:01:00.240
or do other things that make a shiver,

01:01:00.240 --> 01:01:02.670
we lose a lot of that brown fat,

01:01:02.670 --> 01:01:04.250
but what's interesting about brown fat

01:01:04.250 --> 01:01:05.260
is that there's some evidence

01:01:05.260 --> 01:01:08.080
that brown fat just like white fat

01:01:09.080 --> 01:01:11.710
can both increase in size,

01:01:11.710 --> 01:01:14.280
but that you can also add new cells.

01:01:14.280 --> 01:01:15.670
Now, there's a little bit controversial.

01:01:15.670 --> 01:01:17.950
People always say you can't
change the number of fat cells,

01:01:17.950 --> 01:01:21.190
you can just shrink them
or increase their size.

01:01:21.190 --> 01:01:24.660
Well, it turns out that
epinephrin released

01:01:24.660 --> 01:01:27.420
from these little nerve
endings in brown fat

01:01:27.420 --> 01:01:30.750
and succinate circulating in the body may

01:01:30.750 --> 01:01:32.870
and I want to underscore
may have the effect

01:01:32.870 --> 01:01:35.390
of increasing the amount
of brown fat cells

01:01:35.390 --> 01:01:40.360
probably by converting these
beige fat cells into brown fat.

01:01:40.360 --> 01:01:43.290
So that allows us to become
much as we were early in life,

01:01:43.290 --> 01:01:45.580
where we metabolized like crazy

01:01:45.580 --> 01:01:48.660
and we'd heat ourselves
up without shivering.

01:01:48.660 --> 01:01:51.700
Some people have taken the
cold thing to the extreme,

01:01:51.700 --> 01:01:53.690
putting ice packs on
the back of their neck

01:01:53.690 --> 01:01:55.120
throughout the day.

01:01:55.120 --> 01:01:57.820
Did a episode all about
testosterone and estrogen,

01:01:57.820 --> 01:02:02.150
and there's this, let's
just call it a very niche,

01:02:02.150 --> 01:02:04.810
I have to imagine very,
very niche culture of people

01:02:04.810 --> 01:02:07.610
who are wearing literally, I'm not joking.

01:02:07.610 --> 01:02:10.870
They are these cool pack
ice pack underpants.

01:02:10.870 --> 01:02:12.760
They go by a name that I'm
not going to repeat on here,

01:02:12.760 --> 01:02:15.170
but you can find them on Amazon.

01:02:15.170 --> 01:02:17.698
Those are people that are
using cold packs on the body

01:02:17.698 --> 01:02:19.960
and on the groin to
try and increase things

01:02:19.960 --> 01:02:21.143
like testosterone.

01:02:22.395 --> 01:02:24.890
But as well to try and
increase thermogenesis

01:02:24.890 --> 01:02:27.430
and trying to increase their metabolism.

01:02:27.430 --> 01:02:30.310
Just remember if you become cold adapted,

01:02:30.310 --> 01:02:32.190
you're not going to get
the fat burning effects

01:02:32.190 --> 01:02:33.330
to the same degree.

01:02:33.330 --> 01:02:36.130
So cold is a powerful tool for fat loss,

01:02:36.130 --> 01:02:37.590
but you don't want to adapt.

01:02:37.590 --> 01:02:40.080
This is reminiscent of a rule

01:02:40.080 --> 01:02:42.130
that you hear about in endurance exercise

01:02:42.130 --> 01:02:44.040
and in strength exercise as well,

01:02:44.040 --> 01:02:47.810
which is, that you want to use
the minimal effective stimulus

01:02:47.810 --> 01:02:49.850
to promote growth or progress.

01:02:49.850 --> 01:02:52.950
So growth of a muscle or
improvements in endurance.

01:02:52.950 --> 01:02:57.930
If you go 10% further
on a run or 10% faster,

01:02:57.930 --> 01:03:00.510
you will likely see an
improvement in performance

01:03:00.510 --> 01:03:02.520
provided your recovery the
next time you come back

01:03:02.520 --> 01:03:05.610
and do that same round of exercise.

01:03:05.610 --> 01:03:06.930
You'll be able to do more work

01:03:06.930 --> 01:03:08.850
or complete the work
more easily, et cetera.

01:03:08.850 --> 01:03:09.733
You've adapted.

01:03:10.740 --> 01:03:15.410
If you do 20% more distance
or 20% more weight,

01:03:15.410 --> 01:03:18.480
you won't necessarily see the same

01:03:18.480 --> 01:03:21.300
commiserate level of gain or improvement.

01:03:21.300 --> 01:03:23.450
And so likewise with cold,

01:03:23.450 --> 01:03:25.960
if you're quickly moving
from 30 seconds of exposure

01:03:25.960 --> 01:03:27.320
to 10 minutes of exposure,

01:03:27.320 --> 01:03:31.450
you're overlooking the opportunity
to get the most fat loss

01:03:31.450 --> 01:03:34.590
and increase in metabolism
by stepping it up

01:03:34.590 --> 01:03:36.160
in smaller increments.

01:03:36.160 --> 01:03:36.993
Okay?

01:03:36.993 --> 01:03:39.380
And this also speaks to the rationale

01:03:39.380 --> 01:03:42.050
for using cold exposure
to accelerate fat loss

01:03:42.050 --> 01:03:43.170
for certain periods,

01:03:43.170 --> 01:03:45.520
but then maybe not doing it year round.

01:03:45.520 --> 01:03:47.140
If fat loss is your goal,

01:03:47.140 --> 01:03:49.540
maybe use it for two,
three months at a time

01:03:49.540 --> 01:03:51.230
and then stop for two,
three months at a time,

01:03:51.230 --> 01:03:52.840
because it is such a potent stimulus

01:03:52.840 --> 01:03:56.440
provided you engage in the shiver.

