maybe it was in my dreams,

01:12:20.770 --> 01:12:23.040
I don't recall which I
was able to do 60 seconds

01:12:23.040 --> 01:12:23.873
around the track,

01:12:23.873 --> 01:12:25.260
but of course I couldn't
get that on the second

01:12:25.260 --> 01:12:29.760
or third or fourth if I
did that was certainly

01:12:29.760 --> 01:12:32.170
in the fantasy land and not reality.

01:12:32.170 --> 01:12:35.640
But 60 seconds would
be about one revolution

01:12:35.640 --> 01:12:36.473
around the track,

01:12:36.473 --> 01:12:40.200
maybe 90 seconds, depending
on how fast a one is running.

01:12:40.200 --> 01:12:42.620
So 60 to 240 seconds.

01:12:42.620 --> 01:12:44.660
MICT okay.

01:12:44.660 --> 01:12:47.550
This moderate intensity
continuous training

01:12:47.550 --> 01:12:50.970
is steady state cardio
sometimes called Zone 2 cardio

01:12:50.970 --> 01:12:52.630
these days on the internet,

01:12:52.630 --> 01:12:55.640
which has performed continuously
for 20 to 60 minutes

01:12:55.640 --> 01:13:00.070
at moderate intensity
of 40 to 60% of VO2 max

01:13:00.070 --> 01:13:05.070
or if you prefer heart rate
55 to 70% of max heart rate.

01:13:05.270 --> 01:13:06.103
Okay?

01:13:06.103 --> 01:13:08.000
So we can think about high, medium

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:09.610
and low intensity exercise.

01:13:09.610 --> 01:13:12.370
Although low intensity usually means

01:13:12.370 --> 01:13:13.960
that you could carry on a conversation,

01:13:13.960 --> 01:13:16.520
or maybe you have to gasp
every few steps or so,

01:13:16.520 --> 01:13:17.960
while trying to talk and run.

01:13:17.960 --> 01:13:20.350
That's I think going to
be the most useful way

01:13:20.350 --> 01:13:23.150
to have this conversation
that we're having now,

01:13:23.150 --> 01:13:25.180
because there's so many
different forms of exercise

01:13:25.180 --> 01:13:27.653
that people do and intensity is important.

01:13:28.750 --> 01:13:31.270
Let's ask the question
that I think many people

01:13:31.270 --> 01:13:32.423
are wondering about,

01:13:33.490 --> 01:13:34.990
which is, is it better?

01:13:34.990 --> 01:13:38.500
Meaning do you burn more fat
if you do your exercise fasted?

01:13:38.500 --> 01:13:42.060
And fasted in this respect
could be that you wake up

01:13:42.060 --> 01:13:42.893
in the morning,

01:13:42.893 --> 01:13:44.020
you've been fasting all night,

01:13:44.020 --> 01:13:47.040
you just hydrate and you exercise

01:13:47.040 --> 01:13:49.740
or sometimes people will ingest caffeine,

01:13:49.740 --> 01:13:51.760
there's controversy as to whether
or not that quote on quote

01:13:51.760 --> 01:13:52.780
breaks the fast.

01:13:52.780 --> 01:13:54.630
It has to do with whether
or not your caffeine adapted

01:13:54.630 --> 01:13:57.240
something for another episode.

01:13:57.240 --> 01:13:58.990
In any case that would be fasted.

01:13:58.990 --> 01:14:00.990
So probably not having eaten anything

01:14:00.990 --> 01:14:05.192
for anywhere from three to
24 hours or maybe even more.

01:14:05.192 --> 01:14:06.860
As you could also be
fasted in the afternoon.

01:14:06.860 --> 01:14:08.850
If you had lunch at noon and it's four

01:14:08.850 --> 01:14:10.100
or five or 6:00 p.m.

01:14:10.100 --> 01:14:12.230
Is it, will you burn more fat

01:14:12.230 --> 01:14:16.910
if you exercise without
an eating anything first,

01:14:16.910 --> 01:14:18.980
without ingesting any calories first?

01:14:18.980 --> 01:14:21.060
And people have tried to
really split hairs on this,

01:14:21.060 --> 01:14:22.050
every which way people say,

01:14:22.050 --> 01:14:23.730
well, you can fat fast,

01:14:23.730 --> 01:14:25.790
because fat and protein doesn't lead

01:14:25.790 --> 01:14:30.790
to as great increases in
insulin as other things,

01:14:30.820 --> 01:14:33.020
maybe you can have a few
almonds and then still train.

01:14:33.020 --> 01:14:38.020
And indeed insulin will
prevent fat oxidation.

01:14:38.790 --> 01:14:39.690
I want to be really clear.

01:14:39.690 --> 01:14:41.280
The burning part of fat in the cell,

01:14:41.280 --> 01:14:45.630
the movement of the fatty
acid and into mitochondria

01:14:45.630 --> 01:14:49.130
and the conversion ATP,
insulin inhibits that process.

01:14:49.130 --> 01:14:52.500
However, it's been shown

01:14:52.500 --> 01:14:55.380
that it least for short
periods of training,

01:14:55.380 --> 01:14:58.050
it doesn't really seem to
matter whether or not you eat

01:14:58.050 --> 01:15:00.310
before training or you don't,

01:15:00.310 --> 01:15:02.830
if your goal is fat oxidation.

01:15:02.830 --> 01:15:04.610
Now, I want to put an asterix near that,

01:15:04.610 --> 01:15:06.010
because there are some exceptions.

01:15:06.010 --> 01:15:09.707
But there were several studies done that,

01:15:09.707 --> 01:15:12.580
and the kind of the classic ones of these,

01:15:12.580 --> 01:15:14.210
I'll read out to you.

01:15:14.210 --> 01:15:18.240
What they basically did is they
gave people glucose, sugar,

01:15:18.240 --> 01:15:21.930
to increase their blood
sugar before training or not.

01:15:21.930 --> 01:15:25.920
And the kind of classic study
of this is Al Borg at all.

01:15:25.920 --> 01:15:28.080
So in 1976, so it goes way back,

01:15:28.080 --> 01:15:31.420
which is that glucose reduces
fat burning and exercise.

01:15:31.420 --> 01:15:33.700
And then some other studies
if you want to look these up,

01:15:33.700 --> 01:15:35.160
they're very easy to find on PubMed.

01:15:35.160 --> 01:15:37.173
You put in Horowitz 1999,

01:15:38.775 --> 01:15:41.950
[indistinct] is another
one where they have people

01:15:41.950 --> 01:15:43.630
drink milk with glucose in it.

01:15:43.630 --> 01:15:47.500
So sweet sugary milk
before exercise, et cetera.

01:15:47.500 --> 01:15:49.960
And you can find a number of examples

01:15:49.960 --> 01:15:54.220
where eating before exercise
reduces the amount of fat

01:15:54.220 --> 01:15:56.810
that's oxidized during the exercise.

01:15:56.810 --> 01:16:00.513
And you can also find a lot
of studies showing that,

01:16:02.550 --> 01:16:05.810
eating during exercise
or prior to exercise

01:16:05.810 --> 01:16:08.520
will not reduce the amount
of fat that is oxidized.

01:16:08.520 --> 01:16:10.570
However, the types of exercise

01:16:10.570 --> 01:16:13.870
whether I was medium
intensity or high intensity

01:16:13.870 --> 01:16:16.330
or low intensity is all over
the map for these studies.

01:16:16.330 --> 01:16:19.710
So it's very hard to
target an ideal protocol.

01:16:19.710 --> 01:16:22.560
And then if you look really
deep in the literature,

01:16:22.560 --> 01:16:24.540
you start to find meta analysis

01:16:24.540 --> 01:16:27.720
where people have actually
aggregated all the findings

01:16:27.720 --> 01:16:30.050
and some modern studies where it points

01:16:30.050 --> 01:16:32.450
to some very specific
and useful protocols.

01:16:32.450 --> 01:16:35.240
And so here's the rule
that or the protocol

01:16:35.240 --> 01:16:37.403
that I extracted from that literature.

01:16:39.400 --> 01:16:41.580
At a period of about 90 minutes

01:16:42.650 --> 01:16:44.363
of moderate intensity exercise,

01:16:44.363 --> 01:16:46.220
I want to be clear,

01:16:46.220 --> 01:16:51.220
at about or after 90 minutes
of moderate intensity exercise.

01:16:51.220 --> 01:16:53.610
There's a switchover point

01:16:53.610 --> 01:16:57.070
whereby if you ate before the exercise,

01:16:57.070 --> 01:16:58.700
you will reduce, excuse me,

01:16:58.700 --> 01:17:03.700
you will burn far less fat
from the 90 minute point onward

01:17:04.320 --> 01:17:07.820
than you would if you had
gone into the training fasted.

01:17:07.820 --> 01:17:09.250
So let me repeat that.

01:17:09.250 --> 01:17:10.730
If it's moderate intensity,

01:17:10.730 --> 01:17:13.253
so-called zone two cardio type exercise,

01:17:14.300 --> 01:17:16.720
at the 90 minute point,

01:17:16.720 --> 01:17:19.370
if you happen to have
eaten before the exercise

01:17:19.370 --> 01:17:23.160
within one to three hours
prior to the exercise,

01:17:23.160 --> 01:17:26.500
then you reduce the amount
of fat that you will burn

01:17:26.500 --> 01:17:29.040
from 90 minutes onward,

01:17:29.040 --> 01:17:32.060
whereas if you had fasted
prior to the exercise,

01:17:32.060 --> 01:17:34.260
you hadn't eaten anything
for three hours or more prior

01:17:34.260 --> 01:17:35.093
to the exercise.

01:17:35.093 --> 01:17:38.440
At the 90 minute point,
90 minutes of exercise

01:17:38.440 --> 01:17:41.690
you will start to burn
more fat than you would

01:17:41.690 --> 01:17:43.100
had you eaten.

01:17:43.100 --> 01:17:47.680
Now, 90 minutes of moderate
intensity exercises is a lot.

01:17:47.680 --> 01:17:49.740
So that's a pretty long run.

01:17:49.740 --> 01:17:51.840
Even if you're running
at a pretty slow pace

01:17:51.840 --> 01:17:55.430
like a 10 or 12 minute mile,
that's a lot of running,

01:17:55.430 --> 01:17:56.330
that's a lot of swimming.

01:17:56.330 --> 01:17:57.810
So that's a lot of walking,

01:17:57.810 --> 01:17:58.963
that's a lot of hiking.

01:17:59.820 --> 01:18:02.070
However, there are people who
are going out hiking all day

01:18:02.070 --> 01:18:03.750
or running all day or walking all day.

01:18:03.750 --> 01:18:07.040
And if you want to burn
more fat per unit time,

01:18:07.040 --> 01:18:10.400
you want to oxidize more fat
then you would do that fasted.

01:18:10.400 --> 01:18:14.750
Now, there are also studies
that pointed the fact

01:18:14.750 --> 01:18:17.010
that you don't have to wait to 90 minutes

01:18:17.010 --> 01:18:21.250
in order to get this
enhanced fat burning effect.

01:18:21.250 --> 01:18:23.600
The studies I was able to find

01:18:23.600 --> 01:18:26.060
and that looked to me like
quality peer-reviewed studies

01:18:26.060 --> 01:18:30.650
with no company bias or no
product bias of any kind.

01:18:30.650 --> 01:18:32.970
These are studies that were largely funded

01:18:32.970 --> 01:18:37.970
by the federal government
in the university context

01:18:38.080 --> 01:18:42.033
pointed the fact that if one
does high-intensity training,

01:18:43.584 --> 01:18:46.240
or even the very high
intensity forms of training

01:18:46.240 --> 01:18:48.650
like sprints or squats or deadlifts

01:18:48.650 --> 01:18:51.370
or any kind of activity
that can't be maintained

01:18:51.370 --> 01:18:53.360
for more than these, you know, eight

01:18:53.360 --> 01:18:55.290
or I would say up to 60 seconds.

01:18:55.290 --> 01:18:57.840
So a set of lifting
weights repeated, repeated,

01:18:57.840 --> 01:19:01.450
if that's done for
anywhere from 20 minutes,

01:19:01.450 --> 01:19:03.820
so weight training or power lifting

01:19:03.820 --> 01:19:06.070
or these kinds of things
or kettlebell swings

01:19:06.070 --> 01:19:08.660
or up to 60 minutes,

01:19:08.660 --> 01:19:10.660
we'll then the switchover point

01:19:10.660 --> 01:19:12.280
in which you can burn more fat,

01:19:12.280 --> 01:19:15.380
if you go into that fasted comes earlier.

01:19:15.380 --> 01:19:17.890
And this makes sense
because there's nothing holy

01:19:17.890 --> 01:19:21.580
about the 90 minute point
for a medium intensity

01:19:21.580 --> 01:19:23.170
Zone 2 cardio.

01:19:23.170 --> 01:19:25.720
That 90 minute point is the point

01:19:25.720 --> 01:19:30.720
in which the body shifts over
from mainly burning glycogen,

01:19:31.060 --> 01:19:34.490
basically, sugar that comes
from muscles or the liver

01:19:34.490 --> 01:19:37.620
and realizes this is going on for a while,

01:19:37.620 --> 01:19:41.967
I'm going to shift over
to a storage site fuel

01:19:43.420 --> 01:19:46.490
that is in reserve like body fat.

01:19:46.490 --> 01:19:47.770
This is going to happen for a while,

01:19:47.770 --> 01:19:49.610
so I'm going to start
tapping into body fat stores.

01:19:49.610 --> 01:19:51.320
Now, fat doesn't have
a little brain there.

01:19:51.320 --> 01:19:53.540
It is innervated by neurons,
but it doesn't have thoughts.

01:19:53.540 --> 01:19:56.130
And you don't actually control
this switch with your mind.

01:19:56.130 --> 01:19:58.480
This is something that
has to do with the milieu

01:19:58.480 --> 01:19:59.930
of various hormones.

01:19:59.930 --> 01:20:03.870
What has to happen is insulin
has to go down far enough.

01:20:03.870 --> 01:20:05.740
So if you ate before the exercise,

01:20:05.740 --> 01:20:07.330
you'd have an increase in insulin,

01:20:07.330 --> 01:20:08.350
if you ate carbohydrates

01:20:08.350 --> 01:20:11.200
you'd have a bigger increase
in insulin, fat and proteins

01:20:11.200 --> 01:20:13.510
indeed you'll have
lower amounts of insulin

01:20:13.510 --> 01:20:16.520
and fasting will give you
the lowest amount of insulin.

01:20:16.520 --> 01:20:19.810
Well, then that switch over
point is going to come earlier

01:20:19.810 --> 01:20:20.970
in the exercise.

01:20:20.970 --> 01:20:23.590
And if you think about if
you were to do something

01:20:23.590 --> 01:20:26.020
high intensity for 20, 30, 40 minutes,

01:20:26.020 --> 01:20:29.610
so maybe lift weights and
then get into Zone 2 cardio.

01:20:29.610 --> 01:20:31.800
If you are fasted, the literature says

01:20:31.800 --> 01:20:36.030
that you're going to burn
more body fat per unit time

01:20:36.030 --> 01:20:40.370
than if you had eaten before
or during the exercise.

01:20:40.370 --> 01:20:41.203
So what does this mean?

01:20:41.203 --> 01:20:43.450
This means if you want
to burn more body fat,

01:20:43.450 --> 01:20:45.100
if it's in your protocols

01:20:45.100 --> 01:20:47.823
and you have been approved
to do this safely,

01:20:48.830 --> 01:20:53.200
exercise intensely for 20 to 60 minutes,

01:20:53.200 --> 01:20:55.280
the higher the intensity
obviously the shorter

01:20:55.280 --> 01:20:56.550
that about is going to be,

01:20:56.550 --> 01:20:58.660
and then move over into Zone 2 cardio.

01:20:58.660 --> 01:21:01.330
And if you do that fasted or
the medium intensity cardio

01:21:01.330 --> 01:21:02.163
I should say.

01:21:02.163 --> 01:21:04.470
And if you do that fasted,

01:21:04.470 --> 01:21:07.370
then indeed you will burn a
higher percentage of body fat.

01:21:08.790 --> 01:21:11.630
If you need to eat or you
like to eat before you train

01:21:11.630 --> 01:21:14.270
that also can work.

01:21:14.270 --> 01:21:15.980
And if you train very intensely,

01:21:15.980 --> 01:21:20.060
you're likely to shift over
to the fat burning pattern

01:21:20.060 --> 01:21:21.530
more quickly as well.

01:21:21.530 --> 01:21:23.380
So again, this isn't really an issue

01:21:23.380 --> 01:21:25.650
of how long you exercise.

01:21:25.650 --> 01:21:28.540
It's an issue of how
intensely you exercise

01:21:28.540 --> 01:21:31.470
and therefore what fuel
source you're drawing from.

01:21:31.470 --> 01:21:33.150
So hopefully I've made that clear,

01:21:33.150 --> 01:21:35.720
but basically you need to deplete glycogen

01:21:35.720 --> 01:21:38.000
or through high intensity exercise

01:21:38.000 --> 01:21:40.330
and then move to a steady state exercise

01:21:40.330 --> 01:21:42.090
that will allow you to burn more fat.

01:21:42.090 --> 01:21:45.450
Or you need to perform a medium intensity

01:21:45.450 --> 01:21:47.990
or low intensity type exercise
for a long period of time

01:21:47.990 --> 01:21:50.010
before you shift over to burning fat.

01:21:50.010 --> 01:21:53.230
And indeed it seems that
going into all that fasted

01:21:53.230 --> 01:21:56.653
will facilitate the burning
of more fat overall.

01:21:57.800 --> 01:21:59.860
But if you can't even get to the exercise,

01:21:59.860 --> 01:22:02.850
if you're somebody who just
can't do the training at all,

01:22:02.850 --> 01:22:05.965
you're unwilling to or
you're incapable of training,

01:22:05.965 --> 01:22:07.170
unless you eat something,

01:22:07.170 --> 01:22:09.270
then obviously eating
something makes the most sense.

01:22:09.270 --> 01:22:10.700
And what you eat prior to exercise,

01:22:10.700 --> 01:22:13.874
that's a whole other biz
that people argue about

01:22:13.874 --> 01:22:16.040
and fight about whether
or not you should go

01:22:16.040 --> 01:22:19.080
into it with low carbohydrates
or higher carbs, all of that.

01:22:19.080 --> 01:22:21.340
But in general, the theme
there is very simple.

01:22:21.340 --> 01:22:23.710
Which is that you want insulin
levels to be pretty low

01:22:23.710 --> 01:22:26.380
if your goal is body fat reduction,

01:22:26.380 --> 01:22:27.930
if you want to oxidize body fat.

01:22:27.930 --> 01:22:29.260
So fasting in some cases,

01:22:29.260 --> 01:22:30.570
fat fasting and other cases

01:22:30.570 --> 01:22:32.070
where you're just ingesting fats.

01:22:32.070 --> 01:22:34.150
Fat and protein, in some
cases or for some people

01:22:34.150 --> 01:22:35.750
it will be eating carbohydrates.

01:22:35.750 --> 01:22:39.140
I'm not here to dictate a
particular nutrition regimen.

01:22:39.140 --> 01:22:41.250
That's just how the hormone
balance of these things

01:22:41.250 --> 01:22:43.230
and fat oxidation works.

01:22:43.230 --> 01:22:44.860
Now, one thing that's very interesting

01:22:44.860 --> 01:22:47.510
and cannot be overlooked is this issue

01:22:47.510 --> 01:22:51.970
of how much energy you burn
during and after the activity.

01:22:51.970 --> 01:22:53.970
And some of you probably
already know about this,

01:22:53.970 --> 01:22:58.630
but the whole business of
calories in versus calories out,

01:22:58.630 --> 01:23:00.730
and people counting the number of calories

01:23:00.730 --> 01:23:02.500
they burn during their aerobic session

01:23:02.500 --> 01:23:04.810
or during their whatever session

01:23:04.810 --> 01:23:07.050
is only one half of the equation

01:23:07.050 --> 01:23:09.940
and it really eclipses
the more important issue,

01:23:09.940 --> 01:23:14.110
which is how much of an
increase in metabolism

01:23:14.110 --> 01:23:18.570
does a given exercise
create after the exercise?

01:23:18.570 --> 01:23:20.030
And we could talk for hours about this,

01:23:20.030 --> 01:23:21.860
but the simple way to view this is that,

01:23:21.860 --> 01:23:25.080
high intensity training,
anaerobic training

01:23:25.080 --> 01:23:29.200
of weight training, sprints,
burpees, any kind of thing.

01:23:29.200 --> 01:23:31.410
I don't know these days I
hear that you're not supposed

01:23:31.410 --> 01:23:33.280
to do burpees that people
think burpees are dangerous.

01:23:33.280 --> 01:23:35.090
So I'm not suggesting any
particular movements here.

01:23:35.090 --> 01:23:37.090
You have to decide what's right for you.

01:23:38.060 --> 01:23:39.380
I do burpees.

01:23:39.380 --> 01:23:41.180
I don't seem to be injured from them,

01:23:41.180 --> 01:23:43.310
but I hear that they're
terrible for some people.

01:23:43.310 --> 01:23:45.760
So anyway, push-ups, sit-ups,

01:23:45.760 --> 01:23:48.980
whatever it happens to be
that anaerobic exercise

01:23:48.980 --> 01:23:51.630
that's of higher intensity or sprints

01:23:52.810 --> 01:23:55.820
taps into glycogen stores
during the movement

01:23:55.820 --> 01:23:58.900
and we'll burn more energy per unit time

01:23:58.900 --> 01:23:59.830
than moderate intensity.

01:23:59.830 --> 01:24:01.620
High intensity burns more
than modern intensity.

01:24:01.620 --> 01:24:02.770
That's straightforward.

01:24:03.610 --> 01:24:06.840
What's interesting is that all the studies

01:24:06.840 --> 01:24:09.270
that I was able to find on what happens

01:24:09.270 --> 01:24:10.685
after that type of exercise showed

01:24:10.685 --> 01:24:12.990
that the percentage of fat that you burn

01:24:12.990 --> 01:24:16.710
after high intensity
exercise is actually greater.

01:24:16.710 --> 01:24:18.360
In other words, you burn a lot of glycogen

01:24:18.360 --> 01:24:20.150
during the high intensity exercise.

01:24:20.150 --> 01:24:21.940
And then after the exercise,

01:24:21.940 --> 01:24:24.130
the post exercise oxygen consumption

01:24:24.130 --> 01:24:27.240
as it sometimes called goes up.

01:24:27.240 --> 01:24:28.980
We know this after you train intensely

01:24:28.980 --> 01:24:31.230
that post exercise oxygen
consumption goes up

01:24:31.230 --> 01:24:33.920
sometimes for up to 24 hours.

01:24:33.920 --> 01:24:35.620
And it is during that period of time

01:24:35.620 --> 01:24:39.230
that you oxidize more fat not glycogen.

01:24:39.230 --> 01:24:42.930
Now, what's interesting is
that the reverse is also true,

01:24:42.930 --> 01:24:45.200
for people that do long bouts of low

01:24:45.200 --> 01:24:46.930
or moderate intensity exercise.

01:24:46.930 --> 01:24:48.590
So typically this would
be things like running,

01:24:48.590 --> 01:24:49.710
swimming, biking, et cetera.

01:24:49.710 --> 01:24:52.050
So 60, 90 minutes, two hours

01:24:52.050 --> 01:24:53.930
maybe even people that
are training for marathons

01:24:53.930 --> 01:24:55.130
or half marathons,

01:24:55.130 --> 01:24:57.352
when they stop training,

01:24:57.352 --> 01:25:01.640
they burn more glycogen,
more carbohydrate,

01:25:01.640 --> 01:25:05.450
even though they were burning
more body fat per unit time

01:25:05.450 --> 01:25:07.130
during the low intensity exercise.

01:25:07.130 --> 01:25:08.500
So there's this kind of inversion.

01:25:08.500 --> 01:25:10.980
High-intensity burns more
glycogen during the activity,

01:25:10.980 --> 01:25:13.300
more body fat afterwards.

01:25:13.300 --> 01:25:17.250
Moderate to low intensity
burns more percentage-wise

01:25:17.250 --> 01:25:20.210
more body fat is oxidized than glycogen

01:25:21.265 --> 01:25:24.830
during the actual exercise
afterward it's more glycogen.

01:25:24.830 --> 01:25:27.060
So I don't want this
to get too complicated.

01:25:27.060 --> 01:25:30.750
The point is you should
pick exercise that you like,

01:25:30.750 --> 01:25:32.560
that you're going to do regularly,

01:25:32.560 --> 01:25:36.340
but it does seem that the
high intensity exercise

01:25:36.340 --> 01:25:39.320
followed by moderate intensity exercise

01:25:39.320 --> 01:25:41.930
is going to be optimal
for fat burning overall.

01:25:41.930 --> 01:25:45.430
Because when you look at the
percentage of body fat burned,

01:25:45.430 --> 01:25:47.610
and you look at the overall increase

01:25:47.610 --> 01:25:49.470
in basal metabolic rate,

01:25:49.470 --> 01:25:51.630
moderate and high intensity training

01:25:52.610 --> 01:25:54.880
followed by low intensity training

01:25:54.880 --> 01:25:57.580
or even just followed
by going back into life

01:25:57.580 --> 01:26:00.690
is going to be the best way
to continue to burn body fat

01:26:00.690 --> 01:26:03.853
because of the ways that it
increases basal metabolic rate.

01:26:05.040 --> 01:26:07.730
This could be distilled
into a simple protocol

01:26:07.730 --> 01:26:10.370
whereby three or four times a week

01:26:10.370 --> 01:26:13.300
you do high intensity training
followed by either nothing

01:26:13.300 --> 01:26:16.610
or followed by low intensity training

01:26:16.610 --> 01:26:19.500
especially if you're
able to do that fasted.

01:26:19.500 --> 01:26:21.740
And I should just mention
that none of this stuff

01:26:21.740 --> 01:26:23.740
about fasted is about performance.

01:26:23.740 --> 01:26:25.910
If you want to perform really well,

01:26:25.910 --> 01:26:27.834
this is for reasons of performance

01:26:27.834 --> 01:26:30.560
and you want to, you know, it's
for a sport or a competition,

01:26:30.560 --> 01:26:32.200
it's not for body fat purposes.

01:26:32.200 --> 01:26:34.610
Well, then all of this kind of falls away

01:26:34.610 --> 01:26:37.220
and is modified by what's
ideal to eat for performance.

01:26:37.220 --> 01:26:38.210
But what we're talking about today

01:26:38.210 --> 01:26:42.540
is how to optimize body fat loss.

01:26:42.540 --> 01:26:47.540
So train moderately to very high intensity

01:26:48.240 --> 01:26:51.510
and then moderate to low intensity,

01:26:51.510 --> 01:26:53.880
or train moderate to high intensity,

01:26:53.880 --> 01:26:55.160
and then go about life.

01:26:55.160 --> 01:26:59.030
And in fact, I have a friend
who uses this strategy.

01:26:59.030 --> 01:27:00.530
He likes the train intensely

01:27:00.530 --> 01:27:03.180
and not that often protocol
cause he's a very busy person.

01:27:03.180 --> 01:27:05.340
So he'll train for 20
or 30 minutes intensely

01:27:05.340 --> 01:27:08.330
with weights or just body
weight movement doing a lot,

01:27:08.330 --> 01:27:10.620
he does burpees and push-ups
and sit-ups and pull-ups

01:27:10.620 --> 01:27:13.700
and just kind of moving and
kind of circuit type training.

01:27:13.700 --> 01:27:15.170
But where he's breathing really hard,

01:27:15.170 --> 01:27:16.310
the goal he always says is,

01:27:16.310 --> 01:27:18.830
I want to breathe hard
for 30 minutes every day.

01:27:18.830 --> 01:27:21.630
And then afterwards he
hydrates and drinks coffee

01:27:21.630 --> 01:27:22.680
and moves into his day.

01:27:22.680 --> 01:27:24.440
And he's walking around and taking calls

01:27:24.440 --> 01:27:25.880
and carrying around his children

01:27:25.880 --> 01:27:26.850
and doing all these kinds of things

01:27:26.850 --> 01:27:27.683
that keep him really busy

01:27:27.683 --> 01:27:29.460
which is kind of like low intensity work.

01:27:29.460 --> 01:27:31.350
So I think you get the principle now.

01:27:31.350 --> 01:27:33.920
But you should all be asking yourselves

01:27:33.920 --> 01:27:36.380
as scientists of yourselves.

01:27:36.380 --> 01:27:38.940
Why would it be that
certain patterns of exercise

01:27:38.940 --> 01:27:41.640
would lead to more or less fat loss?

01:27:41.640 --> 01:27:44.010
I mean, it can't just be
about the energy burn.

01:27:44.010 --> 01:27:45.550
We already established that.

01:27:45.550 --> 01:27:47.530
And again, it has to do with the neurons.

01:27:47.530 --> 01:27:50.080
It has to do with how we
engage the nervous system.

01:27:50.080 --> 01:27:53.570
So while non-exercise activity
induced thermogenesis, NEAT,

01:27:53.570 --> 01:27:57.600
the fidgeting and cold
can induce thermogenesis

01:27:57.600 --> 01:28:01.070
by engaging shiver tight
movement or low-level movements.

01:28:01.070 --> 01:28:04.490
Big movements that are
of very high intensity,

01:28:04.490 --> 01:28:06.010
meaning they require a lot of effort,

01:28:06.010 --> 01:28:09.820
deploy a lot of adrenaline
epinephrin from our neurons

01:28:09.820 --> 01:28:12.980
and signal particular types

01:28:12.980 --> 01:28:17.980
and amounts of fat
thermogenesis, fat oxidation,

01:28:18.160 --> 01:28:20.500
whereas low level intensity exercise,

01:28:20.500 --> 01:28:22.410
low or moderate intensity exercise,

01:28:22.410 --> 01:28:23.890
walking, running, biking

01:28:23.890 --> 01:28:25.160
where you can do that easily,

01:28:25.160 --> 01:28:27.110
there's not very much adrenaline release.

01:28:27.110 --> 01:28:31.450
So adrenaline aka epinephrin

01:28:31.450 --> 01:28:33.660
is really the final common path

01:28:33.660 --> 01:28:35.920
by which movement of any kind,

01:28:35.920 --> 01:28:37.410
whether or not it's low level shiver,

01:28:37.410 --> 01:28:40.720
whether or not it's lifting
a barbell sprinting up a hill

01:28:40.720 --> 01:28:42.360
or doing a long bike ride.

01:28:42.360 --> 01:28:46.950
Adrenaline is the effector of fat loss.

01:28:46.950 --> 01:28:49.560
It's the trigger end, it's the effector.

01:28:49.560 --> 01:28:52.910
So now I want to turn our
attention to compounds

01:28:52.910 --> 01:28:55.550
that increase epinephrin and adrenaline,

01:28:55.550 --> 01:28:58.290
as well as compounds that work outside

01:28:58.290 --> 01:29:00.770
the adrenaline epinephrin pathway

01:29:00.770 --> 01:29:03.120
to increase the rates of fat loss.

01:29:03.120 --> 01:29:06.210
I almost always save
compounds and supplements

01:29:06.210 --> 01:29:07.990
and things of that sort to the end,

01:29:07.990 --> 01:29:10.840
because I do believe that
people should look first

01:29:10.840 --> 01:29:14.270
towards behavioral tools and
an understanding of the science

01:29:14.270 --> 01:29:17.300
before they look toward a supplement

01:29:17.300 --> 01:29:21.320
or a particular thing that
they can extract from diet.

01:29:21.320 --> 01:29:23.070
This is mainly to try
and shift people away

01:29:23.070 --> 01:29:26.020
from the kind of magic
pill phenomenon or the idea

01:29:26.020 --> 01:29:28.130
that there is a magic pill
because there really isn't.

01:29:28.130 --> 01:29:29.700
And frankly, there never will be.

01:29:29.700 --> 01:29:30.950
But there are some compounds

01:29:30.950 --> 01:29:34.630
that can greatly increase fat
oxidation and mobilization.

01:29:34.630 --> 01:29:38.340
And understanding which
compounds increase oxidation

01:29:38.340 --> 01:29:41.010
or mobilization can be very useful

01:29:41.010 --> 01:29:43.870
if your goal is to accelerate fat loss.

01:29:43.870 --> 01:29:46.370
There are things that people can ingest

01:29:46.370 --> 01:29:50.090
that will allow them to oxidize more fat.

01:29:50.090 --> 01:29:52.580
And that occurs mainly
by increasing the amount

01:29:52.580 --> 01:29:55.160
of epinephrin that is
released from neurons

01:29:55.160 --> 01:29:57.310
that innovate fat tissue.

01:29:57.310 --> 01:29:59.150
One of the more common ones is one

01:29:59.150 --> 01:30:01.823
that you may already be
using which is caffeine.

01:30:02.670 --> 01:30:06.820
It's well-established that
caffeine can enhance performance,

01:30:06.820 --> 01:30:08.280
if you're caffeine adapted.

01:30:08.280 --> 01:30:10.220
I talked about this in an earlier episode

01:30:10.220 --> 01:30:12.170
so I want to make sure
I'm very clear about this.

01:30:12.170 --> 01:30:14.430
If you are not used to drinking caffeine

01:30:14.430 --> 01:30:17.420
and you suddenly decide I'm going to drink

01:30:17.420 --> 01:30:20.170
a big cup of coffee before training,

01:30:20.170 --> 01:30:24.250
you will vasoconstrict and
you will limit performance.

01:30:24.250 --> 01:30:25.530
So that's performance.

01:30:25.530 --> 01:30:28.060
If you're caffeine adapted however,

01:30:28.060 --> 01:30:29.950
there's this kind of
interesting phenomenon

01:30:29.950 --> 01:30:31.670
where ingestion of caffeine

01:30:31.670 --> 01:30:34.700
serves more as a performance enhancer,

01:30:34.700 --> 01:30:36.160
both by increasing alertness,

01:30:36.160 --> 01:30:39.940
but also by way of dilating vasculature

01:30:39.940 --> 01:30:41.340
of allowing more blood flow.

01:30:42.440 --> 01:30:46.720
Now, caffeine for burning
more fat for oxidizing

01:30:46.720 --> 01:30:49.020
and mobilizing more fat
is an interesting one.

01:30:50.050 --> 01:30:54.590
It can be effective at
dosages up to 400 milligrams.

01:30:54.590 --> 01:30:56.950
You have to be careful if
you're caffeine sensitive.

01:30:56.950 --> 01:30:58.980
Some people have just the
littlest bit of caffeine

01:30:58.980 --> 01:31:00.770
and their mind goes crazy,

01:31:00.770 --> 01:31:02.000
and they're very uncomfortable.

01:31:02.000 --> 01:31:04.130
It can have cardiovascular
effects for some people

01:31:04.130 --> 01:31:05.300
or hypertension, et cetera.

01:31:05.300 --> 01:31:07.070
So please check with your doctor.

01:31:07.070 --> 01:31:12.070
But 400 milligrams is roughly
a cup and a half a coffee

01:31:12.210 --> 01:31:13.300
or two cups of coffee.

01:31:13.300 --> 01:31:16.530
Nowadays, there's a lot
more caffeine in coffee.

01:31:16.530 --> 01:31:19.790
So if you go to a typical cafe

01:31:19.790 --> 01:31:22.670
and you were to get their medium-sized

01:31:22.670 --> 01:31:25.250
that would have close
to a gram of caffeine,

01:31:25.250 --> 01:31:28.490
which is why, if you're a
regular caffeine consumer

01:31:28.490 --> 01:31:30.330
and you don't get that gram of caffeine

01:31:30.330 --> 01:31:32.350
in your coffee each day,
you will get a headache.

01:31:32.350 --> 01:31:35.250
It can cause constriction
and dilation of blood vessels

01:31:35.250 --> 01:31:37.050
in ways that's complicated,

01:31:37.050 --> 01:31:39.150
but you'll get a headache.

01:31:39.150 --> 01:31:42.620
Some people like the
way they feel drinking

01:31:42.620 --> 01:31:45.690
100 to 200, 300 maybe 400
milligrams of caffeine

01:31:45.690 --> 01:31:46.523
before training.

01:31:46.523 --> 01:31:49.410
And indeed that will lead
to increase fat oxidation.

01:31:49.410 --> 01:31:52.280
It will do that because you
will release more epinephrin

01:31:52.280 --> 01:31:53.510
and adrenaline.

01:31:53.510 --> 01:31:55.740
So let's just place this in the context

01:31:55.740 --> 01:31:56.870
of what we said previously.

01:31:56.870 --> 01:31:59.520
Let's say you normally do Zone 2 cardio,

01:31:59.520 --> 01:32:02.630
so you're going out for
a moderately intense run

01:32:02.630 --> 01:32:05.090
for 30 to 60 minutes or so.

01:32:05.090 --> 01:32:08.120
I think the current recommendation
guidelines in the States

01:32:08.120 --> 01:32:11.610
are that people engage in 30 minutes

01:32:11.610 --> 01:32:15.850
of moderate intensity
exercise five days a week

01:32:15.850 --> 01:32:18.570
for that's 150 minutes.

01:32:18.570 --> 01:32:20.460
If their goal is to improve

01:32:20.460 --> 01:32:23.393
or maintain health of the
cardiovascular system.

01:32:24.850 --> 01:32:27.950
80% of people in the United
States fail to do that,

01:32:27.950 --> 01:32:29.930
or anything close to it.

01:32:29.930 --> 01:32:32.760
We are way below threshold
for what the government

01:32:32.760 --> 01:32:33.593
has recommended.

01:32:33.593 --> 01:32:35.060
In this case, the
government recommendations,

01:32:35.060 --> 01:32:36.250
I think are pretty good.

01:32:36.250 --> 01:32:38.830
That's one could always
do better of course.

01:32:38.830 --> 01:32:41.500
But 80% of people aren't even doing that.

01:32:41.500 --> 01:32:44.082
However, just using the logic

01:32:44.082 --> 01:32:47.270
and the understanding of
how epinephrin adrenaline

01:32:47.270 --> 01:32:49.520
is affecting this fat oxidation process.

01:32:49.520 --> 01:32:51.990
If you were to go out for 15 minutes

01:32:51.990 --> 01:32:54.420
and you drank caffeine before you went,

01:32:54.420 --> 01:32:58.890
yes, you'll probably oxidize
more fat per unit time.

01:32:58.890 --> 01:33:01.590
Can you compensate for the exercise

01:33:01.590 --> 01:33:04.040
you're not doing just
by drinking caffeine?

01:33:04.040 --> 01:33:07.430
Well, probably if you were
just talking about fat loss,

01:33:07.430 --> 01:33:10.090
if that caffeine makes
you fidget a lot, right?

01:33:10.090 --> 01:33:13.250
The amount of calories that
you burn in a 30 minute run,

01:33:13.250 --> 01:33:14.900
unless the run is very intense

01:33:14.900 --> 01:33:16.940
and you're wearing a weight
vest and it's up a hill,

01:33:16.940 --> 01:33:18.603
it's not that great, right?

01:33:18.603 --> 01:33:20.250
Then you probably get you in somewhere

01:33:20.250 --> 01:33:24.370
into the 400, 500 calories burned area.

01:33:24.370 --> 01:33:27.180
But I said earlier, and
there are a lot of data now

01:33:27.180 --> 01:33:28.600
to support that fidgeting for a day

01:33:28.600 --> 01:33:31.690
can burn anywhere from 800
to 2,500 calories a day.

01:33:31.690 --> 01:33:33.650
So you might say, well,
fidgeting is better than running,

01:33:33.650 --> 01:33:35.720
ah, but it doesn't trigger the activation

01:33:35.720 --> 01:33:37.950
and the positive health effects

01:33:37.950 --> 01:33:39.700
of the cardiovascular system.

01:33:39.700 --> 01:33:42.390
So fidgeting alone can be great,

01:33:42.390 --> 01:33:45.600
but you need exercise for other reasons.

01:33:45.600 --> 01:33:47.243
Caffeine can enhance the amount of fat

01:33:47.243 --> 01:33:50.150
that you burn in any duration of exercise.

01:33:50.150 --> 01:33:52.460
And it can shift the percentage of fat

01:33:52.460 --> 01:33:54.683
that you oxidize compared to glycogen.

01:33:55.630 --> 01:33:59.400
Unless you take that caffeine
and it ramps you up so much

01:33:59.400 --> 01:34:01.630
that you're training
really, really intensely.

01:34:01.630 --> 01:34:02.810
The bottom line is,

01:34:02.810 --> 01:34:06.010
if you like caffeine and
you can use it safely,

01:34:06.010 --> 01:34:09.820
ingesting somewhere between
104 milligrams of caffeine

01:34:09.820 --> 01:34:13.090
prior to exercise somewhere
between 30 to 40 minutes

01:34:13.090 --> 01:34:15.857
before exercise can be beneficial

01:34:15.857 --> 01:34:20.730
if we're talking about fat
oxidation burning more body fat.

01:34:20.730 --> 01:34:22.010
So that's caffeine.

01:34:22.010 --> 01:34:23.100
There are a number of other things

01:34:23.100 --> 01:34:25.600
that have existed over the
years that are in this pathway,

01:34:25.600 --> 01:34:30.600
things like ephedrine which
is now illegal in most states,

01:34:31.070 --> 01:34:32.370
I think maybe an all states

01:34:32.370 --> 01:34:35.330
because people were dropping
dead from taking ephedrine,

01:34:35.330 --> 01:34:37.410
because they were heating up too much.

01:34:37.410 --> 01:34:39.960
It's interesting it wasn't
direct effects on the heart

01:34:39.960 --> 01:34:41.290
causing heart attack.

01:34:41.290 --> 01:34:45.950
It could trigger by way
of adrenergic receptors.

01:34:45.950 --> 01:34:47.400
If you'd like to know,

01:34:47.400 --> 01:34:50.570
increases in body temperature and heat.

01:34:50.570 --> 01:34:53.870
Now, those drugs turned
out to be dangerous,

01:34:53.870 --> 01:34:55.500
because people were overheating and dying.

01:34:55.500 --> 01:34:57.610
There was also the big Fen-Phen craze.

01:34:57.610 --> 01:35:01.260
That was a drug that was
released fenfluramine

01:35:01.260 --> 01:35:03.890
which actually was quite effective

01:35:03.890 --> 01:35:05.640
as an anti obesity drug,

01:35:05.640 --> 01:35:10.130
a treatment for obesity that
had to be outlawed as well.

01:35:10.130 --> 01:35:13.660
It was FDA approval was removed

01:35:13.660 --> 01:35:15.210
because again people were dying

01:35:15.210 --> 01:35:17.040
because of cardiovascular effects.

01:35:17.040 --> 01:35:19.800
I don't know if people were
overheating on it as well.

01:35:19.800 --> 01:35:21.460
So what is the solution?

01:35:21.460 --> 01:35:24.900
If caffeine is the kind of the
entry point for most people

01:35:24.900 --> 01:35:27.040
of using compounds to increase the rate

01:35:27.040 --> 01:35:31.220
or percentage of fat loss in
exercise and even at rest,

01:35:31.220 --> 01:35:33.410
what are some of the other
things that are useful

01:35:33.410 --> 01:35:34.243
and interesting?

01:35:34.243 --> 01:35:36.550
Well, in terms of tools
that are actionable

01:35:36.550 --> 01:35:38.940
and have reasonable safety margins,

01:35:38.940 --> 01:35:43.570
I've talked before about
something called GLP-1.

01:35:43.570 --> 01:35:46.200
This is something that can be triggered

01:35:46.200 --> 01:35:48.687
by the ingestion of yerba
mate, which is a tea,

01:35:48.687 --> 01:35:51.470
and I guess because I'm half Argentine,

01:35:51.470 --> 01:35:52.670
we grew up drinking mate.

01:35:52.670 --> 01:35:54.120
I think I was drinking mate from the time

01:35:54.120 --> 01:35:56.010
I was about three or four years old.

01:35:56.010 --> 01:35:57.450
I don't suggest that for kids.

01:35:57.450 --> 01:36:00.570
I don't think kids should
be ingesting caffeine.

01:36:00.570 --> 01:36:04.830
But anyway I did it and
I still ingest mate.

01:36:04.830 --> 01:36:07.490
Mate increases GLP-1.

01:36:07.490 --> 01:36:10.710
GLP-1 is in the glucagon pathway.

01:36:10.710 --> 01:36:13.080
So let's just quickly
return to our biochemistry.

01:36:13.080 --> 01:36:16.540
As you recall, fat is
mobilized from body fat stores

01:36:17.430 --> 01:36:18.900
and then it's burned up.

01:36:18.900 --> 01:36:20.750
It's oxidized in cells.

01:36:20.750 --> 01:36:24.100
It actually needs to
be converted into ATP.

01:36:24.100 --> 01:36:28.810
And those fatty acids are
essentially converted into ATP

01:36:28.810 --> 01:36:31.070
in the mitochondria of the cell.

01:36:31.070 --> 01:36:34.810
High insulin prevents that from happening

01:36:34.810 --> 01:36:38.423
and glucagon facilitates that process.

01:36:39.580 --> 01:36:41.880
Glucagon facilitates that process

01:36:41.880 --> 01:36:44.500
through increases in GLP-1.

01:36:44.500 --> 01:36:49.330
The short takeaway is mate increases GLP-1

01:36:49.330 --> 01:36:52.630
and yes, increases the percentage
of fat that you will burn.

01:36:52.630 --> 01:36:54.400
It increases fat burning.

01:36:54.400 --> 01:36:55.860
And that is especially true,

01:36:55.860 --> 01:36:57.990
it turns out from the
scientific literature,

01:36:57.990 --> 01:37:02.060
