01:40:41.460 --> 01:40:42.293
We talked about it.

01:40:42.293 --> 01:40:44.490
We did a whole episode on
hormones and metabolism.

01:40:44.490 --> 01:40:46.720
And so for instance, berberine,

01:40:46.720 --> 01:40:50.870
which comes from a plant
or metformin are compounds

01:40:50.870 --> 01:40:54.070
that are now in kind of growing use

01:40:54.070 --> 01:40:55.670
for reducing blood glucose.

01:40:55.670 --> 01:40:58.550
They are very potent at
reducing blood glucose,

01:40:58.550 --> 01:41:00.750
which will reduce insulin because the job

01:41:00.750 --> 01:41:04.390
of the hormone insulin is to
essentially manage glucose

01:41:04.390 --> 01:41:05.570
in the bloodstream.

01:41:05.570 --> 01:41:08.560
So there are a huge gallery of compounds

01:41:08.560 --> 01:41:10.200
that will reduce insulin

01:41:10.200 --> 01:41:12.960
and thereby can increase fat oxidation.

01:41:12.960 --> 01:41:15.350
And that's because, as I mentioned before,

01:41:15.350 --> 01:41:19.010
fat oxidation, this conversion
of fatty acids into ATP

01:41:19.010 --> 01:41:21.520
in the mitochondria is
inhibited by insulin.

01:41:21.520 --> 01:41:22.970
So if you keep insulin low,

01:41:22.970 --> 01:41:25.070
you're going to increase that process.

01:41:25.070 --> 01:41:27.310
Which brings us full circle back

