that is obviously
beneficial to your health,

01:42:05.670 --> 01:42:08.070
but the one that allows you to adhere

01:42:08.070 --> 01:42:12.300
to whatever it is that the
particular nutrition protocol is,

01:42:12.300 --> 01:42:13.133
right?

01:42:13.133 --> 01:42:14.290
If you can't stick with something,

01:42:14.290 --> 01:42:16.020
then it's not very worthwhile.

01:42:16.020 --> 01:42:19.110
But from the purely scientific standpoint,

01:42:19.110 --> 01:42:22.940
there's also an advantage
to keeping insulin low.

01:42:22.940 --> 01:42:24.090
Now, that doesn't necessarily mean

01:42:24.090 --> 01:42:25.700
you go to zero carbohydrate.

01:42:25.700 --> 01:42:28.120
I've talked before about
my preferred way of eating

01:42:28.120 --> 01:42:30.270
is to go lower or no
carbohydrates throughout the day

